Former Abia State Governor, Orji Uzor Kalu, has been freed from prison. He regained freedom on Wednesday after months of incarceration. The Senator walked out of Kuje Correctional Centre after the completion of his release formalities. His Warrant of Release was signed by Justice Liman and transmitted to prison authorities. Liman of the Federal High Court, Lagos, had on Tuesday ordered Kaluâ€™s release. He set aside the trial, conviction and sentence of the former governor to 12 years imprisonment on December 5, 2019.